French Revolution invented the notion of the citizen, but as Spieler shows, it also invented the noncitizen-the person whose rights were nonexistent. Empire and Underworld discovers in Guiana's wilderness a haunting prehistory of current moral dilemmas surrounding detainees of indeterminate legal status. Pairing the history of France with that of its underworld and challenging some of the century's most influential theorists from Hannah Arendt to Michel Foucault, Spieler demonstrates how rights of the modern world can mutate into an apparatus of human deprivation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aCaptivityzFrench GuianaxHistory. 0aMarginality, SocialzFrench GuianaxHistory. 0aMinoritieszFrench GuianaxHistory. 0aPolitical violencezFrench GuianaxHistory. 0aPower (Social sciences)zFrench GuianaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY; POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2012z978311029371508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2012z9783110288971oZDB-23-DPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674062870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674062870.jpg